logical portraits of people confronted with harsh choices and a coming-of-age story underscored by the deep involvement of sexuality and violence. Interspersed are flights of philosophical consideration of the relationship between Christians and Jews, love and suffering, justice and forgiveness. A major addition to the canon of literature bearing witness to the Holocaust in the Soviet Union, Redemption is an important reckoning with anti-Semitism and Stalinist repression from a significant Soviet Jewish voice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aRussian language materials. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBromfield, Andrew.1 aDraitser, Emil.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060660708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/gore1851440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231546027423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231546027.jpg  a978-3-11-060660-7  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK 